node.title: Baytown, Texas Shooting Leaves One Dead, 14 Injured at Vigil
node.alt: Stock photo. A gunman opened fire at a vigil in Baytown, Texas, killing one and injured 14 people.
node.description: A woman was holding a vigill for her son who was killed at his home when the suspect drove down the road shooting into the crowd in Baytown, Texas.
node.content:
["One person is dead and 14 others were are injured after a shooting at a vigil in Baytown, Texas, on Sunday night, authorities said.", "A gunman opened fire on a large crowd participating in a celebration of life, Harris County Sheriff Ed Gonzalez said in a tweet.", "KTRK reported that a woman was holding a vigil for her son who was killed at his home when the suspect drove down the road shooting into the crowd.", "\"@HCSOTexas units responded to 1403 N Market Loop. Preliminary info: a large crowd gathered for a celebration of life,\" Gonzalez tweeted. \"A vehicle approached and someone from the vehicle began shooting into the crowd. At least 8 people sustained injuries; 7 are non-fatal, but one has been pronounced at a hospital. Homicide & Crime Scene Investigators are en route.\"", "In a follow-up tweet, Gonzalez added: \"Update to shooting on N. Market Loop: told the number of wounded individuals is now up to 14; 1 has been pronounced deceased, 3 being taken by Lifeflight in critical condition, and the remaining ones are said to have non/fatal injuries.\"", "This is a breaking news story and will be updated.", "", "
Stock photo. A gunman opened fire at a vigil in Baytown, Texas, killing one and injured 14 people.
"]
